---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="PMO Resources — Lavelle Pty Ltd"
  description="Battle-tested PMO product packs, templates and free tools from Lavelle Pty Ltd. Steering Committee Pack, Project Recovery Pack, Business Case Pack and more."
  currentNav="pmo-resources"
>
  <!-- SUB-PAGE HERO -->
  <section class="subhero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="subhero__crumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a> &nbsp;/&nbsp; <span>PMO Resources</span>
      </div>
      <h1>The PMO artefacts we use on engagement. <em>Now packaged.</em></h1>
      <p class="subhero__lead">
        Project managers, PMO leads and program directors don't need another framework — they need a steering committee pack that's ready for Monday. These are the exact artefact sets Lavelle deploys on engagement, structured for download and immediate use. Built by senior practitioners, tested on real programs, written in language an executive will actually read.
      </p>
      <div class="hero__ctas" style="margin-top:2.5rem;">
        <a href="#packs" class="btn btn--primary">View the product packs <span class="btn__arrow">→</span></a>
        <a href="#checklist" class="btn btn--ghost">Download the free checklist</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FREE TOOL -->
  <section id="checklist" style="background:var(--paper); padding:clamp(3rem,6vw,5rem) 0;">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="checklist-grid">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow">Free · for delivery leads</div>
          <h2 style="font-size:var(--display-md); margin:1.25rem 0 1rem; font-weight:500;">
            The <em style="color:var(--ochre);">Project Recovery Checklist.</em>
          </h2>
          <p class="lead" style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
            Twenty-three diagnostic questions we ask in the first forty-eight hours of any recovery engagement. Print it, take it into your next steering meeting, and you'll know within an hour where the real problems live — and which ones can wait.
          </p>
          <ul style="list-style:none; display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:0.6rem; margin-bottom:2rem;">
            <li style="font-size:var(--body-sm); color:var(--ink-soft); padding-left:1.25rem; position:relative;">
              <span style="position:absolute; left:0; color:var(--ochre); font-weight:700;">✓</span>23 diagnostic questions across 5 categories
            </li>
            <li style="font-size:var(--body-sm); color:var(--ink-soft); padding-left:1.25rem; position:relative;">
              <span style="position:absolute; left:0; color:var(--ochre); font-weight:700;">✓</span>Scoring rubric &amp; severity matrix
            </li>
            <li style="font-size:var(--body-sm); color:var(--ink-soft); padding-left:1.25rem; position:relative;">
              <span style="position:absolute; left:0; color:var(--ochre); font-weight:700;">✓</span>Stakeholder interview prompts
            </li>
            <li style="font-size:var(--body-sm); color:var(--ink-soft); padding-left:1.25rem; position:relative;">
              <span style="position:absolute; left:0; color:var(--ochre); font-weight:700;">✓</span>One-page summary template
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <form style="background:var(--bone); border:1px solid var(--rule); padding:2.5rem;">
          <h3 style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif; font-size:1.4rem; font-weight:500; margin-bottom:0.5rem;">
            Send it to me.
          </h3>
          <p style="font-size:var(--body-sm); color:var(--ink-soft); margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
            No newsletter signup wall. We'll send the PDF and one email a fortnight with new field notes. Unsubscribe anytime.
          </p>
          <label
            style="display:block; font-size:var(--micro); letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--sage); margin-bottom:0.5rem;"
          >
            First name
          </label>
          <input
            type="text"
            placeholder="Your name"
            style="width:100%; padding:0.85rem 1rem; border:1px solid var(--rule); background:var(--paper); font-family:inherit; font-size:var(--body); margin-bottom:1.25rem;"
          />
          <label
            style="display:block; font-size:var(--micro); letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--sage); margin-bottom:0.5rem;"
          >
            Work email
          </label>
          <input
            type="email"
            placeholder="you@organisation.gov.au"
            style="width:100%; padding:0.85rem 1rem; border:1px solid var(--rule); background:var(--paper); font-family:inherit; font-size:var(--body); margin-bottom:1.5rem;"
          />
          <button type="submit" class="btn btn--primary" style="width:100%; justify-content:center;">
            Send me the checklist <span class="btn__arrow">→</span>
          </button>
        </form>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PRODUCT PACKS -->
  <section id="packs">
    <div class="wrap">
      <header class="section__head">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow">Product packs</div>
          <h2 class="section__title" style="margin-top:1.25rem;">
            Four packs.<br />One <em>delivery system.</em>
          </h2>
        </div>
        <p class="lead">
          Each pack is a self-contained artefact set for one decision-critical moment in delivery. Buy individually, or take the four-pack bundle and run your entire program governance from a single, coherent system.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="products">
        <article class="product">
          <span class="product__tag">Available now · v1.2</span>
          <h3 class="product__title">Steering Committee Pack</h3>
          <p class="product__desc">
            A complete steering committee toolkit. Decision papers, status dashboards, escalation logs and meeting protocols, built to make the boardroom 30 minutes count.
          </p>
          <ul class="product__list">
            <li>12 board-ready templates (.docx, .xlsx, .pptx)</li>
            <li>Decision-paper writing guide</li>
            <li>Pre-read protocol &amp; agenda framework</li>
            <li>RAID escalation thresholds</li>
            <li>RAG dashboard design with real definitions</li>
            <li>30-page implementation playbook</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="product__footer">
            <div>
              <div class="product__price">$147</div>
              <div class="product__price-sub">single user · AUD · GST inc.</div>
            </div>
            <a href="#" class="btn btn--primary">Buy now <span class="btn__arrow">→</span></a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="product">
          <span class="product__tag">Coming Q3</span>
          <h3 class="product__title">Project Recovery Pack</h3>
          <p class="product__desc">
            The full 30-day diagnostic and stabilisation playbook for project managers stepping into a red program. The exact cadence Lavelle uses on recovery engagement.
          </p>
          <ul class="product__list">
            <li>30-day recovery roadmap</li>
            <li>Health-check diagnostic instrument</li>
            <li>Stakeholder &amp; sponsor scripts</li>
            <li>Re-baseline communication kit</li>
            <li>Vendor and team realignment protocols</li>
            <li>Recovery decision paper template</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="product__footer">
            <div>
              <div class="product__price">$197</div>
              <div class="product__price-sub">single user · AUD · GST inc.</div>
            </div>
            <a href="#" class="btn btn--ghost">Join waitlist <span class="btn__arrow">→</span></a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="product">
          <span class="product__tag">Coming Q4</span>
          <h3 class="product__title">Business Case Pack</h3>
          <p class="product__desc">
            Treasury-grade and ICT business case templates and supporting models. Strategic, outline and full business case stages, with the benefits logic and risk articulation a board can actually interrogate.
          </p>
          <ul class="product__list">
            <li>Strategic, outline and full business case templates</li>
            <li>Structured for executive and delegate approval</li>
            <li>Benefits realisation model</li>
            <li>Options analysis framework</li>
            <li>Cost &amp; sensitivity workbook</li>
            <li>Executive narrative writing guide</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="product__footer">
            <div>
              <div class="product__price">$197</div>
              <div class="product__price-sub">single user · AUD · GST inc.</div>
            </div>
            <a href="#" class="btn btn--ghost">Join waitlist <span class="btn__arrow">→</span></a>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="product">
          <span class="product__tag">Coming Q4</span>
          <h3 class="product__title">Procurement Pack</h3>
          <p class="product__desc">
            RFP design, evaluation governance and vendor onboarding artefacts. Built for procurement events where probity, capability assessment and speed have to coexist.
          </p>
          <ul class="product__list">
            <li>RFP &amp; EOI templates with evaluation criteria library</li>
            <li>Probity-compliant scoring workbook</li>
            <li>Vendor due diligence checklist</li>
            <li>Contract schedule design guide</li>
            <li>Vendor onboarding &amp; kickoff toolkit</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="product__footer">
            <div>
              <div class="product__price">$197</div>
              <div class="product__price-sub">single user · AUD · GST inc.</div>
            </div>
            <a href="#" class="btn btn--ghost">Join waitlist <span class="btn__arrow">→</span></a>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>

      <!-- BUNDLE -->
      <div class="bundle">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow" style="color:var(--ochre); border-color:var(--ochre);">Best value · all four packs</div>
          <h3 style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif; font-size:2.25rem; font-weight:500; line-height:1.05; margin:1rem 0; color:var(--bone);">
            The PMO Four-Pack.<br /><em style="color:var(--ochre); font-style:italic; font-weight:300;">Your entire delivery system, one bundle.</em>
          </h3>
          <p style="color:rgba(244,239,230,0.78); font-size:var(--body-lg); margin-bottom:1.5rem; max-width:50ch;">
            All four packs — Steering Committee, Project Recovery, Business Case and Procurement — at a single bundle price. Save $191 over individual purchase.
          </p>
          <ul style="list-style:none; color:rgba(244,239,230,0.78); font-size:var(--body-sm); display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:0.5rem; margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
            <li>· Lifetime access to current and future versions</li>
            <li>· Free template updates as standards evolve</li>
            <li>· Enterprise licensing available (5-seat / 25-seat / unlimited)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div style="text-align:right;">
          <div style="font-size:var(--micro); color:rgba(244,239,230,0.55); letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; margin-bottom:0.5rem;">
            Was $738
          </div>
          <div style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif; font-size:clamp(3rem,6vw,5rem); font-weight:300; color:var(--ochre); line-height:1; margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
            $797
          </div>
          <a href="#" class="btn btn--primary" style="background:var(--ochre); border-color:var(--ochre); color:var(--bone);">
            Pre-order the bundle <span class="btn__arrow">→</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ENTERPRISE LICENSING -->
  <section style="background:var(--paper);">
    <div class="wrap">
      <header class="section__head">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow">Enterprise licensing</div>
          <h2 class="section__title" style="margin-top:1.25rem;">
            For PMOs.<br />For <em>whole departments.</em>
          </h2>
        </div>
        <p class="lead">
          Standardise your governance artefacts across an entire team, function or agency. Multi-seat licensing includes branded versions, training sessions and direct support from Lavelle.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="enterprise-grid">
        <div style="background:var(--bone); border:1px solid var(--rule); padding:2.5rem;">
          <div class="eyebrow">Team licence</div>
          <div style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif; font-size:3rem; font-weight:300; color:var(--ochre); margin:1rem 0 0.5rem; line-height:1;">
            $3,000<span style="font-size:1rem; color:var(--ink-soft);">/yr</span>
          </div>
          <p style="font-size:var(--body-sm); color:var(--ink-soft); margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
            Up to 10 users · all four packs · annual updates
          </p>
          <ul style="list-style:none; display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:0.5rem; font-size:var(--body-sm); color:var(--ink-soft);">
            <li>· All four packs, all updates</li>
            <li>· 10 named seats</li>
            <li>· Co-branded option</li>
            <li>· Email support</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div style="background:var(--bone); border:2px solid var(--ochre); padding:2.5rem; position:relative;">
          <div
            style="position:absolute; top:-12px; right:1.5rem; background:var(--ochre); color:var(--bone); font-size:var(--micro); padding:0.3rem 0.8rem; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase;"
          >
            Most popular
          </div>
          <div class="eyebrow">Department licence</div>
          <div style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif; font-size:3rem; font-weight:300; color:var(--ochre); margin:1rem 0 0.5rem; line-height:1;">
            $5,500<span style="font-size:1rem; color:var(--ink-soft);">/yr</span>
          </div>
          <p style="font-size:var(--body-sm); color:var(--ink-soft); margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
            Up to 50 users · all packs · onboarding workshop
          </p>
          <ul style="list-style:none; display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:0.5rem; font-size:var(--body-sm); color:var(--ink-soft);">
            <li>· All four packs, all updates</li>
            <li>· 50 named seats</li>
            <li>· Co-branded versions</li>
            <li>· Half-day onboarding workshop</li>
            <li>· Priority support</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div style="background:var(--bone); border:1px solid var(--rule); padding:2.5rem;">
          <div class="eyebrow">Agency licence</div>
          <div style="font-family:'Fraunces',serif; font-size:3rem; font-weight:300; color:var(--ochre); margin:1rem 0 0.5rem; line-height:1;">
            $8,000<span style="font-size:1rem; color:var(--ink-soft);">/yr</span>
          </div>
          <p style="font-size:var(--body-sm); color:var(--ink-soft); margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
            Unlimited users · branded · with quarterly advisory
          </p>
          <ul style="list-style:none; display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:0.5rem; font-size:var(--body-sm); color:var(--ink-soft);">
            <li>· All four packs, all updates</li>
            <li>· Unlimited seats within agency</li>
            <li>· Fully branded artefacts</li>
            <li>· Full-day onboarding workshop</li>
            <li>· Quarterly advisory call with Sky</li>
            <li>· Government panel listing eligible</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="text-align:center; margin-top:3rem;">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn--primary">Request enterprise pricing <span class="btn__arrow">→</span></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ENGAGE -->
  <section class="engage">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="engage__grid">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow">Need more than templates?</div>
          <h2 style="margin-top:1.25rem;">When the artefact isn't enough, <em>bring us in.</em></h2>
          <p class="lead" style="margin-top:1.5rem;">
            The packs are designed to be self-serve. But sometimes a program needs a senior practitioner in the room — not another document. If that's where you are, the next conversation is the consulting team's.
          </p>
          <div class="hero__ctas" style="margin-top:2.5rem;">
            <a href="/consulting" class="btn btn--primary">See consulting services <span class="btn__arrow">→</span></a>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn" style="background:transparent; color:var(--bone); border:1px solid var(--bone);">
              Talk to Sky directly
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <ul class="engage__list">
          <li><a href="#"><span>Bulk &amp; enterprise licensing</span><span>→</span></a></li>
          <li><a href="#"><span>Government panel arrangements</span><span>→</span></a></li>
          <li><a href="#"><span>Co-branded artefact packs</span><span>→</span></a></li>
          <li><a href="#"><span>Training &amp; onboarding workshops</span><span>→</span></a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .checklist-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .bundle {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    background: var(--ink);
    color: var(--bone);
    padding: 3rem;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .enterprise-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }
  @media (min-width: 880px) {
    .checklist-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1.3fr 1fr;
      gap: 5rem;
    }
    .bundle {
      grid-template-columns: 1.5fr 1fr;
      gap: 4rem;
    }
    .enterprise-grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 2rem;
    }
  }
</style>
